**PIXYZ:**  
\-Software that allows CAD models to be brought into video game engines like UNITY, UNREAL ENGINE, etc  
\-Pixyz is not a scanning tool but its a pipeline optimization tool that optimizes CAD models for real time engines  
\-Pixyz can handle these large CAD data/files and import those models into UNITY  
\-Can import CAD, BIM, mesh and point cloud models  
\-It preserves geometry, hierarchy, materials and metadata  
\-Does not directly support fusion 360 but you can export your model from fusion 360 into a format pixyz supports(STEP, FBX, OBJ, IGES, GLTF) and then import it into pixyz  
\-Pixyz can run scripts and batch processing using APIs  
\-Turning engineering CAD into VR showrooms  
\-Creating digital twins  
\-Converting product models into interactive configurators

**Part 2: Workflows**

\-PIXYZ can import GLTF format files on certain versions and with some limitations  
\-Version 2.0 allows GLTF and imports and exports, as well as GLB  
\-Optional but you can convert GLTF files to a compatible format first to import

\-For the first workflow, when you scan your object, you can import to blender if it’s an FBX file, then export to unity  
\-If it’s a cad file, it would have to be taken to Pixyz first  
\-Either option is valid

\-Blender is free and open source while Pixyz is $2,450 per year  
\-Blender’s interface is more complex and Pixyz has a more simpler interface for optimization tasks  
\-Pixyz specializes in geometry optimization for cad data and is optimized in handling larger datasets efficiently better than Blender; Blender is still good too but not better  
\-Blender is flexible  
\-More sources are leaning on using Blender

\-For the second workflow, you can start with a cad file and then use Pixyz to optimize it to take it to unity  
\-Apparently you can also export a FBX from fusion 360 into unity, as seen in a youtube video  
\-It’s achievable but not greatly optimized  
\-Reducing detail like, too many polys and merging parts  
\-It is not real time friendly  
\-So exporting FBX from fusion 360 to Blender to optimize it, then taking it to unity would be better fix

\-For the third workflow, there are AI tools that can generate or enhance 3D models  
\-Meshy and Luma AI are two examples  
\-AI can reduce polys  
\-It can also generate UV’s and textures  
\-These AI’s can export GLB, FBX, OBJ, STL  
\-Has the fastest workflow  
\-Least control but is good for prototyping

\-Pixyz cannot rig, skin, or create maps  
\-Pixyz can play animations but can’t edit them  
\-Pixyz can only import and export animations  
\-Animation editing must be done in Blender or Maya  
\-Pixyz is mainly a conversion and optimization tool

